    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Adding to other answers already given above. If case insensivity is of any importance to you, then use Jackson. Gson does not support case insensitivity for key names, while jackson does.</p>\n\n<p>Here are two related links</p>\n\n<p>(No) Case sensitivity support in Gson : \n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6332651/gson-how-to-get-a-case-insensitive-element-from-json\">GSON: How to get a case insensitive element from Json?</a></p>\n\n<p>Case sensitivity support in Jackson\n<a href=\"https://gist.github.com/electrum/1260489\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://gist.github.com/electrum/1260489</a></p>\n"
  } ],
